@page "/not-found"
@layout MainLayout

@*
    FU-2 — also rendered by UseStatusCodePagesWithReExecute("/not-found")
    when any page sets Response.StatusCode = 404 (e.g. CaseDetail.razor on
    a foreign-tenant or unknown case id). Styled to match the rest of the
    Inspection pages (inspection-page-header / inspection-section). Body
    text is deliberately generic — never name the resource type, never
    echo the requested URL — so we don't disclose tenant existence.
*@

<PageTitle>Not found — Inspection v2</PageTitle>

<header class="inspection-page-header">
    <div>
        <h1>Page not found</h1>
        <p class="inspection-page-subtitle">
            The page or resource you requested does not exist or you do not have access to it.
        </p>
    </div>
</header>

<section class="inspection-section">
    <p class="inspection-empty">
        Try the <a href="/">Overview</a> or the <a href="/cases">Cases</a> list.
    </p>
</section>
